In a #small pot{}, combine @basmati rice{1/2%cup}, @water{3/4%cup}, and a pinch of
@salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil; cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is
tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a small pot{} over medium-high heat.
Add @cauliflower rice{12%oz} and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Cook, stirring
occasionally, until softened and any excess liquid has absorbed,
~{6-8%minutes}. Turn off heat; stir in @butter{1%tbsp} until melted. Keep
covered off heat until ready to serve.

Wash and dry produce. Trim @green beans{6%oz} if necessary; halve crosswise.
Halve, peel, and thinly slice @yellow onion{1}. Peel and mince or grate @ginger{1%thumb}
until you have 1 tsp. Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}. Roughly chop
@cilantro{1/4%oz}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add
green beans, onion, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until
veggies are softened, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Stir in ginger, garlic, @curry powder{1%tbsp}, and half the
@garam masala{1%tsp}. Cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in @chickpeas{1%400g can} and their liquid, coconut milk{1%can}, and
@veggie stock concentrate{2}. Stir in @sugar{1/2%tsp}. Bring to a simmer, then
reduce heat to low; cook, stirring occasionally, until thickened,
~{4-5%minutes}. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

> If curry seems too thick, stir in a splash of water.

Fluff rice with a fork.

Divide rice and curry between #bowls{}; garnish with cilantro. Serve.